DataElement.preferredName: Biospecimen Availability Metadata Collaboration Required Flag java.lang.Boolean
DataElement.preferredDefinition: Any material sample taken from a biological entity for testing, diagnostic, propagation, treatment or research purposes, including a sample obtained from a living organism or taken from the biological object after halting of all its life functions. Biospecimen can contain one or more components including but not limited to cellular molecules, cells, tissues, organs, body fluids, embryos, and body excretory products.:The quality of being obtainable or accessible and ready for use or service.:Data about data; information that describes another set of data._The process by which two or more parties work jointly towards a common goal.:Something that is necessary; condition, something that is obligatory.:An indicator that can be set or unset in order to signal whether a particular condition is true._Generic value domain for a primitive java datatype that is a Boolean value (true or false).
